BankAccount Encapsulation

Description
This Java program demonstrates the concept of encapsulation. A BankAccount class is created with private fields accountNumber, accountHolderName, and balance. Public getter and setter methods are provided to access and update these fields, with validation to prevent negative balances.

Objectives

To understand encapsulation in Java

To demonstrate controlled access to private fields using getters and setters

To validate and protect object data

Program Details

BankAccount class contains private fields: accountNumber, accountHolderName, balance

Getter and setter methods for each field

Setter for balance rejects negative values

How to Run

Open the project in VS Code

Compile the program using: javac BankReport.java

Run the program using: java BankReport

Output
The program displays the details of three BankAccount objects and demonstrates validation for negative balances.

